    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level E46 M3, featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six with crisp individual throttle body response. This specimen boasts a flawless subframe reinforcement and a fully overhauled VANOS system for peak variable valve timing precision. The drivetrain is anchored by a tactile ZF 6-speed manual and a tight limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque vectoring. Suspension geometry is dialed with Bilstein dampers, while the braking system utilizes high-friction pads on cross-drilled rotors. Meticulously maintained with a documented service history, this is a turnkey example of German engineering at its zenith.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. Zero cosmetic flaws. Full service history. Low mileage.",
      "price": 45000.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Presenting a truly exceptional example of automotive preservation. This vehicle is in showroom condition, having been meticulously maintained in a climate-controlled garage since day one. The exterior finish is flawless, boasting a deep, mirror-like luster with a professional ceramic coating protection and absolutely zero stone chips, scratches, or door dings. Inside, the cabin remains in an 'as-new' state; the premium leather upholstery is supple with no signs of bolster wear, and the original factory scent persists. Every electronic component, from the high-fidelity sound system to the intricate climate controls, functions perfectly. Mechanically, the car is beyond reproach, featuring a complete, documented service history from authorized dealerships. It drives with the same precision and tightness as it did the day it left the assembly line, with no rattles, leaks, or deferred maintenance of any kind. This is a rare opportunity for a discerning collector or enthusiast to own a peak-condition specimen that stands out even among the finest examples. Includes two original keys, the factory window sticker, and a comprehensive binder of all service records.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 12
    },
    {
